It seems APIM‚Äôs Managed Identity uses the resource-based (v1) token flow, which issues tokens with iss=https://sts.windows.net/<tenantId>/ and ver=1.0.
VEG appears to be configured for v2 token validation, so it rejects the MI-issued token with ‚ÄúJwt issuer is not configured.‚Äù

Current Blocker:
Issuer version mismatch between the token (v1) and the VEG validation (v2).


update VEG to trust the v1 issuer (https://sts.windows.net/<tenantId>/) and JWKS (https://login.windows.net/<tenantId>/discovery/keys).
